  "final_answer": "## Segment-Level FCF Proxy Analysis — Q1 2026\n\n**Note:** All figures reflect the recast consolidated entity (including xAI merged Feb 2, 2026 and X Holdings merged into xAI Mar 28, 2025) for all historical periods presented. No period reflects standalone SpaceX operations exclusively.\n\n### Q1 2026 Segment Data (Three Months Ended March 31, 2026, in $ millions)\n\n| Metric | Space | Connectivity | AI |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Segment Adjusted EBITDA | $(351) | $2,087 | $(609) |\n| Capital Expenditures | $1,052 | $1,332 | $7,723 |\n| **FCF Proxy (Adj. EBITDA − Capex)** | **$(1,403)** | **$755** | **$(8,332)** |\n\n### Calculation: Connectivity FCF Proxy vs. AI Capex\n\n**Step 1 — Annualize Connectivity FCF Proxy at Q1 2026 run-rate:**\n$755M × 4 = **$3,020 million**\n\n**Step 2 — Annualize AI Capex at Q1 2026 run-rate:**\n$7,723M × 4 = **$30,892 million**\n\n**Step 3 — Years of Connectivity annualized FCF proxy to fund one year of AI capex:**\n$30,892M ÷ $3,020M = **10.23 years**\n\n### Answer\n\nIt would take approximately **10.23 years** of Connectivity's annualized Q1 2026 FCF proxy ($3.02 billion/year) to fund one year of AI segment capex at the Q1 2026 run-rate ($30.89 billion/year). This stark ratio underscores the extraordinary capital intensity of the AI segment — driven by xAI's GPU cluster and data-center buildout — which vastly exceeds the cash-generating capacity of the Connectivity (Starlink) segment, even though Connectivity is the only segment producing positive FCF proxy.\n\n{\n  \"sources\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm\",\n      \"name\": \"SpaceX S-1 Filing (May 20, 2026)\"\n    }\n  ]\n}",
